# Agentic runtime boundaries

Use this module when model-driven behavior can call tools or produce a side effect.

- Grant every tool the minimum permission and resource scope required.
- Validate tool arguments in deterministic code and treat model output as untrusted.
- Require human approval before destructive, irreversible, costly, or externally visible actions.
- Define bounded consumption for calls, tokens, loops, time, and money.
- Record the escalation path when permission, data classification, or expected impact is unclear.
- Test misuse and denial paths, not only successful tool calls.

These records describe intended boundaries. Applied AI Rig is not a runtime policy engine and cannot enforce
authorization or human approval by itself.
